			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: The Secret World Has Low Sales and Lousy  Retention
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1756899">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>PPatty</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1756512#post1756512" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Tried it in beta, seemed repetitive, even by MMO standards. <br />
<br />
Also ran sluggishly on my system. Note to MMO makers: Your graphics engine should be generations BEHIND the cutting edge if you want widespread adoption. As in, stop requiring discrete graphics cards to play your games. Yeah, I know it's heretical to hardcore gamers, but there aren't really that many of them.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I could run it near at max on a laptop and if you put it in DX9 mode low end computer can max it fairly easy.<br />
<br />
As it being repetitive, it had the most diversity in quests in any mmo I have ever played. The story and lore elements in TSW are miles beyond any competitor. I think it is just too hard for people, and that the majority just used spoiler sites for the quests. TSW  being the first mmo I have played with what seemed like &quot;quests&quot; and not just &quot;tasks&quot;.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
